definitions.definition: The action of the verb to park .
examples: Parking in central London can be very difficult.

definitions.definition: Space in which to park a car or other vehicle, such as a parking lot or curbside parking.
examples: It can be difficult to find parking in central London.
They found his car in a parking thirty miles away; apparently it had been stolen by a joyrider.

main_definition: The action of the verb to park .
secondary_definitions: Space in which to park a car or other vehicle, such as a parking lot or curbside parking.
